File: lichen/subsys/lichen/coap/coap_keys.c
Lines: 595-617

The ISO 8601 timestamp encoder has a logic issue where 'month' and 'day' may not be set for certain edge cases:

```c
uint8_t month = 1;
uint8_t day;  // UNINITIALIZED
...
for (int m = 0; m < 12; m++) {
    ...
    if (days < mdays) {
        month = m + 1;
        day = days + 1;
        break;
    }
    days -= mdays;
}
```

If 'days' after year processing equals or exceeds the total days in a year (e.g., due to overflow or leap year miscalculation), the loop completes without setting 'day'. Also, if days == 0 on entry, month stays 1 and day is set to 1 (correct), but this is coincidental.

Impact: Garbage timestamp strings in edge cases.

Category: CORRECTNESS - uninitialized variable
